      <Content>The expression θάμβος γὰρ περιέσχεν αὐτόν in {S:04200500900006} is a clear example of a syntactic structure being formally the converse of the semantic structure. One may say amazement seized him, but clearly it is the person who experiences the amazement.</Content>
